    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "Normally when you&#39;re mocking things, it implies that you don&#39;t much care about the concrete object; that you only really care about the behavior of the mocked object.  Perhaps you want to do an integration test instead?  Or, could you provide a rationale as to why you want mocked and concrete objects living together?"
