    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Addition to @Dev Blanked answer, if you want to use an existing bean that was created by Spring the code can be modified to:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@RunWith(MockitoJUnitRunner.class)\npublic class DemoTest {\n\n    @Inject\n    private ApplicationContext ctx;\n\n    @Spy\n    private SomeService service;\n\n    @InjectMocks\n    private Demo demo;\n\n    @Before\n    public void setUp(){\n        service = ctx.getBean(SomeService.class);\n    }\n\n    /* ... */\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This way you don't need to change your code (add another constructor) just to make the tests work.</p>\n"
  }, {
