    "question_id" : 20270391,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I know this is an old question, but we were faced with the same problem when trying to inject Strings. So we invented a JUnit5/Mockito extension that does exactly what you want: <a href=\"https://github.com/exabrial/mockito-object-injection\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/exabrial/mockito-object-injection</a></p>\n\n<p>EDIT:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@InjectionMap\n private Map&lt;String, Object&gt; injectionMap = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();\n\n @BeforeEach\n public void beforeEach() throws Exception {\n  injectionMap.put(\"securityEnabled\", Boolean.TRUE);\n }\n\n @AfterEach\n public void afterEach() throws Exception {\n  injectionMap.clear();\n }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
